# Cabin Rentals of Georgia — AI Agent Rules
# Last updated: 2026-04-03 (Level 59: The Iron Sentry)

## Project Identity

This is the Next.js frontend for Cabin Rentals of Georgia (CROG),
a luxury cabin rental company in Blue Ridge, GA. The site is a
pixel-accurate rebuild of a 20-year-old Drupal CMS, migrated to
Next.js 14 + Tailwind CSS + FastAPI backend.

Production URL: https://frontend-next-topaz.vercel.app
Legacy URL: https://www.cabin-rentals-of-georgia.com

---

## Design System & Typography Protocol

### ⚠ CRITICAL — NEVER use generic Tailwind typography

DO NOT use default Tailwind text sizing classes for body content:
  ❌ text-sm, text-base, text-lg, text-xl, text-2xl, text-3xl
  ❌ prose-sm, prose-base, prose-lg, prose-xl

ALWAYS use the legacy design tokens defined in `tailwind.config.ts`:
  ✅ prose-legacy (for all rich HTML content)
  ✅ text-legacy-h1, text-legacy-h2, text-legacy-h3, text-legacy-body
  ✅ text-legacy-body, text-legacy-heading, text-legacy-link

### Exact Design Tokens (extracted via Playwright getComputedStyle)

Source: `design_tokens.json` (generated by `backend/scripts/extract_computed_css.py`)

```
Font Family:     "Fanwood Text", serif
Body Text:       16px / 20.8px line-height (1.3) / 400 weight
Body Color:      #533e27  — rgb(83, 62, 39)

H1:              35.2px / 35.2px line-height / 400 weight / italic / color #7c2c00
H2:              27.2px / 27.2px line-height / 400 weight / italic / color #7c2c00
H3:              20.8px / 20.8px line-height / 400 weight / normal  / color #533e27
H4:              16px   / 20.8px line-height / 700 weight / normal  / color #533e27

Link Color:      #7c2c00 — rgb(124, 44, 0) — underlined
Link Hover:      #b7714b
Strong Color:    #7c2c00 — 700 weight
Accent BG:       #faf6ef — warm cream (used for cards, review backgrounds)
Border Color:    #e8dcc8 — warm tan (used for card borders, separators)

H1 Margins:      15px top, 10px bottom
H2 Margins:      22.576px top, 22.576px bottom
H3 Margins:      15px top, 15px bottom
P Margins:       16px top, 16px bottom
LI Margin:       8px bottom
```

### When Building New Components

1. For any rich HTML content (articles, descriptions, blog posts):
   - Use `<ProcessedHTML>` with className `"prose prose-legacy max-w-none"`
   - NEVER add inline color/size overrides — `prose-legacy` handles everything

2. For section headings rendered as React elements:
   - H1: `className="italic text-[#7c2c00]"` — the globals.css `.block h1` handles sizing
   - H2: `className="text-[#7c2c00] italic"` — font-size 170%, line-height 100%
   - H3: `className="text-[130%]"` — uses body color

3. For body text outside prose:
   - Use `text-[#533e27]` — this is the canonical body text color
   - NEVER use `text-gray-700`, `text-slate-600`, or any Tailwind gray scale

4. For cards and panels:
   - Background: `bg-[#faf6ef]`
   - Border: `border-[#e8dcc8]`
   - NEVER use `bg-gray-50`, `bg-white`, or `border-gray-200`

5. For links:
   - Color: `text-[#7c2c00]`
   - Hover: `hover:text-[#b7714b]`
   - Underlined by default
   - NEVER use `text-blue-600` or any blue link color

6. For buttons (primary CTA):
   - Background: `bg-[#7c2c00]`
   - Text: `text-white`
   - Hover: `hover:bg-[#8d3a00]`

---

## Legacy HTML Handling

All HTML from the backend may contain legacy Drupal markup.
ALWAYS pipe body content through `stripLegacyHtml()` from
`@/lib/utils/html-utils` before rendering with `<ProcessedHTML>`.

The stripper removes:
  - Duplicate `<h1 class="title">` tags
  - `div.social-share` (Facebook/Twitter/Pinterest buttons + scripts)
  - `div.cabin-bottom-right` (sidebar)
  - `div.view-testimonials` / `div.view-calls-to-action` blocks
  - Inline `<script>` tags
  - Structural Drupal wrappers (cabin-bottom, cabin-content, etc.)

React components (LikeSaveButton, CabinReviews, Specials cards)
replace these legacy blocks — they are NEVER rendered from HTML.

---

## Component Architecture

- Pages render in `app/(public)/` using Next.js App Router
- Cabin detail: `app/(public)/cabin/[...slug]/page.tsx`
- Activity detail: `app/(public)/activity/[...slug]/page.tsx`
- Blog detail: `app/(public)/blog/[year]/[month]/[day]/[slug]/page.tsx`
- API client: `lib/api/` — axios-based, hitting FastAPI backend
- Backend: FastAPI at `https://api.cabin-rentals-of-georgia.com`

